      "writtenOn": "2018-06-25T20:27:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we want to avoid std::vector in this code, for performance reasons. SkSTArenaAlloc (used below) is probably better. The template argument is a fixed size block that\u0027s stored in the object, and if the allocation fits in there, it never needs to use the heap, otherwise it does a heap allocation. Picking a default size is sort of arbitrary - if we can catch the majority of uses with the stack buffer (maybe 100 verts?), then it\u0027s a big win. Also, one ArenaAlloc can be used to make multiple allocations, and it will try to reuse blocks (it tends to over-allocate), so it might make sense to just hoist \"outerAlloc\" up here, and use that for the deformed points.\n\nSimilarly for the concatenated bone matrices, you could make another SkSTArenaAlloc that pre-allocates for some small but typical number of bones (32?)...",
      "revId": "8684af2f32766ea266e0a2ab268ff8ac6f6fe841",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
